<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="576" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,577,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1477,1504]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the species is dedicated to the Inca people, as the specimen was found at Machu Picchu, near the most prominent icon of the Inca civilization.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="576" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,577,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1549,1576]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kaydan &amp; Szita" authorityName="Kaydan &amp; Szita" authorityYear="2020" box="[329,740,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ripersiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incarum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[329,552,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Ripersiella incarum</emphasis>
Kaydan &amp; Szita
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[748,812,1549,1575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[748,812,1549,1575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be recognized by the combination of the following features: (i) antenna 5 segmented; (ii) circulus absent; (iii) bitubular ducts of one size on dorsum, distributed in longitudinal single rows on medial, submedial and marginal area; (iv) multilocular pores absent; and (v) tubular ducts absent. 
<taxonomicName authority="Szita &amp; Benedicty &amp; Kondo &amp; Ramos-Portilla &amp; Kaydan, 2020" authorityName="Szita &amp; Benedicty &amp; Kondo &amp; Ramos-Portilla &amp; Kaydan" authorityYear="2020" box="[238,463,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ripersiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incarum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[238,463,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Ripersiella incarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[472,537,1657,1683]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[472,537,1657,1683]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Tinsley, 1899" authorityName="Tinsley" authorityYear="1899" box="[689,867,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ripersiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caledonensis">
<emphasis box="[689,867,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">R. caledonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Tinsley, 1899" authorityName="Matile-Ferrero" authorityYear="1976" box="[924,1039,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ripersiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boharti">
<emphasis box="[924,1039,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">R. boharti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lacking circuli, but differs from them both in lacking multilocular pores and tubular ducts and in having 5-segmented antennae (multilocular pores and tubular ducts present, antennae 6 segmented in 
<taxonomicName authority="Tinsley, 1899" authorityName="Kozar &amp; Konczne Benedicty" authorityYear="2003" box="[735,919,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ripersiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caledoniensis">
<emphasis box="[735,919,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">R. caledoniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Tinsley, 1899" authorityName="Matile-Ferrero" authorityYear="1976" box="[976,1090,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ripersiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boharti">
<emphasis box="[976,1090,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">R. boharti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Szita &amp; Benedicty &amp; Kondo &amp; Ramos-Portilla &amp; Kaydan, 2020" authorityName="Szita &amp; Benedicty &amp; Kondo &amp; Ramos-Portilla &amp; Kaydan" authorityYear="2020" box="[1114,1338,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ripersiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incarum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1114,1338,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Ripersiella incarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1410,1729,1755]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1410,1729,1755]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Williams)" authorityName="Tinsley" authorityYear="1899" baseAuthorityName="Williams" box="[320,626,1765,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ripersiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gombakensis">
<emphasis box="[320,498,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">R. gombakensis</emphasis>
(Williams)
</taxonomicName>
in lacking multilocular pores and tubular ducts, but differs in lacking a circulus and having 5-segmented antennae (circulus present and antennae 6 segmented in 
<taxonomicName authority="Tinsley, 1899" authorityName="Tinsley" authorityYear="1899" box="[1157,1333,1801,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ripersiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gombakensis">
<emphasis box="[1157,1333,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">R. gombakensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
